gomodel:SYNGO_2697  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.2: \"Stargazin ΔC Reduces Hippocampal Excitatory Synaptic Currents\"\nFig.3: \"Overexpression of Stargazin ΔC::GFP Increases the Mobility of GluR1 and GluR2 Subunits in Neuronal Membrane\"\nFig.4: \"Stargazin Is Involved in AMPAR Stabilization at Synaptic Sites\"\nFig.6: \"Stargazin Stabilizes AMPAR in Neuronal Membrane through Its Specific Interaction with PSD-95\"\nFig.7: \"Stargazin Diffusion Is Reduced on PSD-95 Clusters\"\nFig.8: \"Stargazin and AMPARs Diffuse as Complexes in the Synaptic and Extrasynaptic Membrane\". Experimental description: Species (after correspondence with author):\nNeuronal culture: mouse\nStargazin construct: mouse\nPSD-95 construct: rat" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5676-366X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9783-5183" ;
